Reasoning: The paper deals with the theoretical study of self-assembly models and fractals, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY). The comparison of two different models, aTAM and 2HAM, also involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the study of hierarchical growth and self-similarity relates to the field of data structures (cs.DS).
